item.description: Lea Michele is an American entertainer, artist, lyricist, and creator. She started her profession as a kid entertainer on Broadway, showing up in creations of Les Misérables (1995-1996), Jazz (1997-1999), Fiddler on the Rooftop (2004-2005), and Spring Arousing (2006-2008). Michele came to unmistakable quality playing Rachel Berry on the Fox series Happiness (2009-2015), for which she got an Emmy Grant designation, two Brilliant Globe selections and won four Individuals’ Decision Grants, three Youngster Decision Grants and a Satellite Honor.

item.title: Logan Paul Reflects On How He Fractured His Relationship With The Rock
item.description: Logan Paul‘s past actions continue to haunt him, as one of them resulted in him losing a good relationship with The Rock, who is now on the TKO Board of Directors. In 2017, Paul posted a controversial video stream while in Japan, where he visited the Suicide Forest. Paul later took the video down and apologized, but the damage had already been done. On the most recent episode of IMPAULSIVE, the current WWE United States Champion opened up about his past relationship with The Rock and why the two men are no longer on speaking terms.

item.title: The One Request Kristen Wiig Made On SNL While Parodying Jamie Lee Curtis' Commercials
item.description: Highlights Kristen Wiig's iconic characters on SNL, like Penelope and the Target Clerk, were inspired by real people she observed in her life. Wiig ate real Activia yogurt during her skit parodying Jamie Lee Curtis' commercials, but requested a switch to regular yogurt for the second scene. Wiig feels more comfortable playing characters on stage than speaking as herself, as she finds public speaking and socializing in large groups to be challenging.

item.title: This 'Friends' Star Spent His Last $230 To Audition For The Show
item.description: Throughout its history, 'Friends' had several guest spots. For the most part, those that appeared on the show went on to enjoy great success, and that especially includes Eddie Cahill, aka Tag. Appearing on the show would open several new doors and since then, he has established quite the TV resume.

item.title: Mariah Carey's 'Glitter' Soundtrack Hits Number One On iTunes
item.description: Mariah Carey’s Glitter, a film loosely based on the legendary singer’s life, was critically and commercially panned upon its release. However, thanks to her devoted fans known as the Lambily, there’s no stopping the 2001 film. The Lambily started the #JusticeForGlitter Twitter hashtag to show their appreciation for the film, and thanks to their devotion, the LP is back on the charts. The album is reportedly at number one on the iTunes album charts.

item.title: Vijayakanth Obituary
item.description: Esteemed Tamil actor and politician Vijayakanth, fondly known as “Captain” by his admirers, passed away this morning at a private hospital in Chennai, India. At 71 years old, the veteran actor had been grappling with pneumonia since November 20, and his health further complicated as he tested positive for COVID-19. Reports from Indian news portals indicated that he was on ventilatory support before his demise. Vijayakanth made his cinematic debut in 1979 with the film “Inikkum Ilamai” and went on to amass a significant body of work, featuring in 154 films.

item.description: Joseph Evans Brown (July 28, 1891 – July 6, 1973) was an American actor and comedian who is most known for his affable film demeanour, quick wit, and infectious grin on screen. He was one of the most popular American comedians throughout the 1930s and 1940s, thanks to films such as A Midsummer Night’s Dream, Earthworm Tractors, and Alibi Ike, which were all hits at the box office. item.description: Flipping out over house flipping. Home renovation shows have quickly become a go-to for TV fans. One of the first popular shows about house flipping, Flip This House, debuted on A&E Network in 2005. HGTV quickly got in on the fun with Flipping Virgins, Flip or Flop and more. Even Bravo starting airing several construction-themes shows in 2007 with the premiere of Jeff Lewis’ Flipping Out, which wrapped in 2018.

item.description: Indra Nooyi Biography Born in Madras, India, Indra Nooyi is an Indian-American business executive and former CEO of PepsiCo. She has consistently ranked among the world’s 100 most powerful women, In 2014, she was ranked at number 13 on the Forbes list of The World’s 100 Most Powerful Women, and was ranked the 2nd most powerful woman on the Fortune list in 2015. Indra Nooyi Age Indra was born on October 28, 1955, in Madras, India.

item.title: Taylor Swift Handled The Boos At Her Friend's Wedding In The Best Way Possible
item.description: Highlights Taylor Swift faced boos from her own fans for avoiding them at a wedding, but we can't blame her for prioritizing her friend's special day. Swift was booed by rival NFL fans when her ad played at MetLife Stadium, but she isn't bothered by the hate and remains unfazed. Swift knows how to deal with negative publicity by avoiding articles that won't contribute positively to her life and not letting internet criticism affect her.

item.title: The Real Reason Jamie Lee Curtis Was Reluctant To Work With Jake Gyllenhaal
item.description: Jamie Lee Curtis became the original scream queen when she first starred in John Carpenter’s Halloween back in 1978, which later became one of the longest-running horror movie franchises of all time. Since then, Curtis has appeared in more than 80 movies and TV shows. She’s also written multiple children's books, started two podcasts, and won an Academy Award for her performance in Everything Everywhere All At Once. Over her career, Curtis has made good friends with many celebrities, from her Freaky Friday co-star Lindsay Lohan to none other than Arnold Schwarzenegger, who she worked with in the movie True Lies.

item.title: 'Teen Mom 2' Alum Jenelle Evans, Mom Barbara's Ups and Downs
item.description: Teen Mom 2 alum Jenelle Evans and her mom, Barbara Evans, have been feuding over custody of Jenelle’s son, Jace — in addition to many other issues — for over a decade. After giving birth to her eldest son in August 2009, Jenelle signed over legal custody of Jace to her mom. The dramatic decision played out on the former MTV personality’s 2010 episode of 16 and Pregnant. At the time, the North Carolina native realized that she needed her mom’s help in raising Jace while she partied with friends.

item.title: Andy Cohens Son Calls Raquel Leviss TomTom Sweatshirt Pretty'

What do you think?” the Bravo executive producer, 54, asked his eldest via Instagram Stories on Thursday, April 13, as Benjamin touched the shimmering material. “It’s so pretty.” After the little one agreed that the black pullover was “pretty” with its gold logo, Cohen added, “Wow, there’s a lot of drama going on with that sweatshirt, Ben.

Today, however, it does seem like Miller is back, recently joining the cast of Netflix limited series Anatomy of a Scandal (where she starred alongside Rupert Friend and Michelle Dockery).

item.title: Nikki Finke Net Worth At Time Of Death
item.description: Nikki Finke had an estimated net worth of $4 million at the time of her death. Nikki Finke was an American blogger, journalist, publisher and writer. She was a consultant to Penske Business Media LLC and senior editorial contributor for PBM run by media owner Jay Penske. Finke’s take-no-prisoners style angered many of showbiz’s top players and delighted others. She often scored huge exclusives, and when they were confirmed by comms teams or publicists, Finke would update her story using her signature “TOLDJA!

item.title: Sona Jobarteh Net Worth, Income, Salary, Earnings, Biography
item.description: Template: a number of problems Born in Gambia and raised in England, Sona Jobarteh is the first female kora player to come from a Griot family. She is also a singer, multi-instrumentalist, and composer with roots in both Gambia and England. Griot family from West Africa, where she was born in 1983 to one of the five main Kora-playing Griot families in the world. She is the granddaughter of Amadu Bansang Jobarteh, the Master Griot of his generation, and the cousin of the well-known and famous Kora player Toumani Diabate.
